'''心盛'''（{{lang-en|flourishing}}），是[[正向心理學|正向心理學]]的重要概念之一，其指一種完全、高度心理健康的表徵。例如，心盛的人常充滿熱情活力，並且無論在個人生活及社會互動之中，均能發揮主動積極、參與的正向功能。也就是有意義和目的過活，而不是僅是存在這世界而已<ref name="ref1">{{cite book |last= Keyes |first= Corey L. M. |coauthors= Jonathan Haidt |title= ''Flourishing: Positive Psychology and the Life Well-lived'' |publisher= American Psychological Association] |year= 2003 |isbn= 1-55798-930-3 }}</ref>
<ref name="ref4">{{cite journal en |last= Keyes |first= Corey L. M. |title=The mental health continuum: From languishing to Flourishing in life |url= https://archive.org/details/sim_journal-of-health-and-social-behavior_2002-06_43_2/page/207 |journal= Journal of Health and Social Behavior |volume=43 |year=2002 |pages=207-222 }}</ref><ref name="ref5">{{cite journal en |last= Fredrickson |first= Barbara L. |coauthors= Marcial F. Losada |title=Positive affect and the complex dynamics of human flourishing |journal= American Psychologist |volume=60 |year=2005 |pages=678-686 }}</ref>。在整體人口群當中，心盛的人相對是少數比例。但大部份處在中度心理健康(moderate mental health)狀態的人們如果能夠透過[[群體介入|群體介入]]的方式，進而達到心盛的階段<ref name="ref3">{{cite journal en |last= Huppert |first= Felicia A. |title=A new approach to reducing disorder and improving well-being |journal= Perspectives on Psychological Science |volume=4 |year=2009 |pages=108-111 }}</ref>。如此，將成為一個較具有健康、生產性、創業的、創造力、參與度等之社會<ref name="ref2">{{cite book |last= Huppert |first= Felicia A. |coauthors= Nick Baylis & Barry Keverne |title= ''The Science of Well-Being'' |publisher= Oxford University Press] |year= 2005 |isbn= 0-19856-752-9 }}</ref>。


